You are loading project context from the Memory Bank. Follow the steps below.

## Step 1 — Identify the task type

Ask the user (or infer from the current conversation) which task type applies:

- **new-feature** — starting something new
- **planning** — architecture or design decisions
- **debugging** — fixing a bug or investigating an issue
- **new-session** — first message of a session or unfamiliar codebase
- **continuing** — resuming from a previous session

## Step 2 — Read the relevant files

Based on the task type, read only the files listed below. Do not read files that are not relevant.

| Task type | Files to read |
|---|---|
| new-feature | `memory-bank/projectbrief.md`, `memory-bank/activeContext.md` |
| planning | `memory-bank/projectbrief.md`, `memory-bank/systemPatterns.md`, `memory-bank/techContext.md` |
| debugging | `memory-bank/techContext.md`, `memory-bank/progress.md`, `memory-bank/activeContext.md` |
| new-session | All files in `memory-bank/` |
| continuing | `memory-bank/activeContext.md`, `memory-bank/progress.md` |

## Step 3 — Summarise what was loaded

After reading, provide a brief summary (3–5 bullet points) of the most relevant context for the current task. Do not reproduce the full file contents.

## Step 4 — Confirm readiness

State: "Memory bank loaded for [task type]. Ready to proceed."
